name: Barbell Overhead Press
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder height with an overhand grip.
Engage your core and press the barbell overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Pause briefly at the top, then lower the barbell back to shoulder height under control.

name: Dumbbell Seated Overhead Press
steps: Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing forward.
Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended above your head.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height with control.

name: Dumbbell Incline Bench Press
steps: Lie on an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended above your chest.
Lower the dumbbells to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle.
Press the dumbbells back up to the starting position.

name: Cable Low Single Arm Lateral Raise
steps: Stand sideways to a low pulley, holding the handle with the hand farthest from the machine.
With a slight bend in your elbow, raise your arm laterally until it is parallel to the floor.
Lower the handle back to the starting position with control.

name: Dumbbell Incline Chest Flys
steps: Lay flat on an incline bench with your feet on the ground.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand above your chest with your arms extended.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest.
Bring the dumbbells back together above your chest by reversing the motion.

name: Kettlebell Single Arm Press
steps: Lie on your back on a flat bench, holding a kettlebell in one hand at chest level.
Press the kettlebell upward until your arm is fully extended.
Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position with control.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Band Single Arm Pec Fly
steps: Anchor a resistance band at shoulder height.
Stand sideways to the anchor point, holding the band handle in the hand farthest from the anchor.
With a slight bend in your elbow, pull the band across your body until your hand is in front of your chest.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Chin Ups
steps: Grab a pull-up bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart.
Hang fully extended.
Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar.
Lower yourself back to the starting position with control.

name: Cable Bayesian Curl
steps: Stand facing away from a low pulley cable machine, holding a handle in one hand.
Step forward to create tension, allowing your arm to extend behind you.
Curl the handle towards your shoulder.
Slowly extend your arm back to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Curl
steps: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended.
Curl the weights while contracting your biceps.
Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl
steps: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended, palms facing your torso.
Curl the weights while keeping your palms facing inward.
Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Wrist Curl
steps: Sit on a bench with your forearm resting on your thigh or a flat surface, palm facing upward.
Hold a dumbbell in your hand, allowing it to roll down to your fingers.
Curl the dumbbell upward by flexing your wrist.
Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Wrist Extension
steps: Sit on a bench with your forearm resting on your thigh or a flat surface, palm facing downward.
Hold a dumbbell in your hand, allowing your wrist to flex downward.
Raise the dumbbell by extending your wrist upward.
Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.

name: Cable Wrist Curl
steps: Sit or stand in front of a low pulley cable machine, holding the handle with your palm facing upward.
Rest your forearm on your thigh or a flat surface, allowing your wrist to extend downward.
Curl the handle upward by flexing your wrist.
Slowly return to the starting position.

name: Kettlebell Wrist Curl
steps: Stand upright, holding a kettlebell in each hand with your arms extended by your sides, palms facing inward.
Flex your wrists to curl the kettlebells upward toward your forearms.
Slowly lower the kettlebells back to the starting position.

name: Landmine Oblique Twist
steps: Place one end of a barbell into a landmine attachment or securely in a corner.
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding the other end of the barbell with both hands.
With arms extended, rotate your torso to one side, lowering the barbell towards your hip.
Engage your obliques to rotate the barbell to the opposite side, following a controlled arc.
Repeat the movement, alternating sides.

name: Oblique Crunch
steps: Lie on your side with knees bent and stacked.
Place your hands behind your head, elbows flared out.
Engage your obliques to lift your upper body towards your hips.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement.
Lower back down with control.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Oblique Pushdown
steps: Set the cable just over your head and attach a handle.
Stand sideways to the machine, grasping the handle with the hand farthest from the machine.
Push the handle down until your elbow is extended, engaging your obliques.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Crunches
steps: Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor.
Place your hands behind your head, elbows pointing outward.
Engage your core by drawing your belly button toward your spine.
Lift your head and shoulders off the floor, curling towards your knees.
Pause briefly at the top, then lower back down with control.

name: Ring Standing Roll Out
steps: Stand facing the rings, grasping them with your arms extended and shoulders away from your ears.
Engage your core and roll forward onto your toes, extending your body while keeping arms straight.
Roll out as far as you can while maintaining control and core engagement.
Return to the starting position by reversing the motion.

name: Band Crunch
steps: Anchor a resistance band above head height.
Kneel down, facing away from the anchor point, holding the band handles at shoulder level.
Push your hips back, flexing at the spine to perform a crunch motion.
Squeeze your abs at the bottom of the movement.
Extend at the hips and spine to return to the starting position.

name: Barbell Squat
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Place the barbell across your upper back, gripping it with both hands.
Maintain the natural arch in your back and engage your core.
Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your chest up and back straight.
Descend until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.

name: Smith Machine Squat
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart under the bar of a Smith machine.
Place the bar across your upper back and shoulders, gripping it with both hands.
Maintain the natural arch in your back and engage your core.
Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your chest up and back straight.
Descend until your thighs are parallel to the floor.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.

name: Kettlebell Step-Up
steps: Stand up straight facing a bench or step.
Hold a kettlebell in one hand, letting it hang by your side.
Place one foot onto the bench, ensuring your entire foot is on the surface.
Push through the heel of the foot on the bench to lift your body upward.
Bring your trailing leg up to the bench, standing tall.
Step back down with the trailing leg first, followed by the lead leg.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Barbell Calf Raises
steps: Place the barbell on your upper back, gripping it securely with both hands.
Stand with your feet flat on the ground, shoulder-width apart.
Extend your heels upwards, lifting them off the ground while keeping your knees stationary.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement.
Lower your heels back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Dumbbell Calf Raises
steps: Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended by your sides.
Position the balls of your feet on top of a weight plate or elevated surface to extend the range of motion.
Raise your heels upwards, lifting them off the ground while keeping your knees stationary.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement.
Lower your heels back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Kettlebell Calf Raises
steps: Stand straight with a kettlebell in each hand, arms fully extended by your sides.
Raise your heels upwards, lifting them off the ground while keeping your knees stationary.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement.
Lower your heels back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: TRX Calf Raises
steps: Hold the TRX straps under your arms, with the handles positioned in your armpits.
Lean forward against the straps, keeping your body straight.
Initiate the calf raise by pushing through the balls of your feet, lifting your heels upwards.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement.
Lower your heels back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Pull-Up
steps: Grasp the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Hang with your arms fully extended and your legs slightly forward, engaging your core.
Pull your body upward by driving your elbows down and back, bringing your chin above the bar.
Pause briefly at the top, then lower yourself back to the starting position with control.

name: Lat Pulldown
steps: Adjust the machine to fit your body and select an appropriate weight.
Sit down and grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and chest up.
Pull the bar down towards your upper chest by driving your elbows down and back.
Pause briefly at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
steps: Lie on a bench with your upper back and shoulders supported, feet flat on the floor.
Hold a dumbbell with both hands above your chest, arms slightly bent.
Lower the dumbbell behind your head in an arc, keeping your elbows slightly bent.
Stretch as far as comfortable, then pull the dumbbell back to the starting position.

name: Single-Arm Dumbbell Row
steps: Place one knee and the same-side hand on a bench for support, with your other foot flat on the floor.
Hold a dumbbell in your free hand, arm extended toward the floor.
Pull the dumbbell upward toward your hip, keeping your elbow close to your body.
Pause at the top, then lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Silverback Shrug
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of you, just past shoulder width.
Bend forward at the hips with a slight bend in your knees, keeping your back flat.
Allow your arms to hang straight down, palms facing each other.
Shrug your shoulders upward toward your ears, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Hold briefly at the top, then lower your shoulders back to the starting position.

name: Dumbbell Row Bilateral
steps: Grab both dumbbells and hinge forward at the hips, keeping a flat back.
Position your torso as close to parallel with the ground as comfortable.
Let your arms hang straight down, palms facing each other.
Pull both dumbbells upward toward your torso, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Pause briefly at the top, then lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.

name: Kettlebell Silverback Shrug
steps: Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at your sides.
Lean forward at the hips, keeping your back flat and arms straight.
Lift your shoulders backward, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Hold briefly at the top, then return to the starting position.

name: Back Extension
steps: Position yourself on the Roman chair with your hips supported and your feet secured.
Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head.
Bend forward at the waist, lowering your upper body towards the floor while keeping your back straight.
Raise your upper body back to the starting position by contracting your lower back muscles.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Superman
steps: Lie face down on the floor with your arms extended in front of you and your legs straight.
Simultaneously raise your arms, legs, and chest off the floor, contracting your lower back muscles.
Hold the position briefly.
Lower your arms, legs, and chest back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs.
Keep your knees slightly bent and your back straight.
Hinge at the hips to lower the dumbbells along the front of your legs, going as low as your flexibility allows.
Contract your lower back and hamstrings to raise your torso back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Fly
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight.
Let the dumbbells hang down beneath you with your palms facing each other.
With a slight bend in your elbows, raise the dumbbells out to the sides until your arms are parallel to the floor.
Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Band Rear Delt Fly
steps: Anchor two resistance bands at a high point and stand between them with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Grasp the handles with your arms extended in front of you at shoulder height, palms facing each other.
With a slight bend in your elbows, pull the bands outward and backward, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Continue until your arms are extended out to your sides.
Return to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Kettlebell Rear Delt Row
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips, bringing your torso close to parallel with the ground, keeping your back straight.
Let the kettlebell hang straight down from your shoulders.
Pull the kettlebell towards your chest, keeping your elbows flared out to the sides.
Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Tricep Dips
steps: Hold your body with arms locked above the equipment.
Lower your body slowly while leaning forward, flaring out your elbows.
Once your shoulders are below your elbows, push yourself back to the starting position using your triceps.

name: Overhead Dumbbell Extension
steps: Sit on a bench and hold a dumbbell with both hands.
Raise the dumbbell overhead at arm's length, holding the weight up with the palms of your hands.
Lower the dumbbell behind your head by breaking at the elbows.
Extend your elbows and flex your triceps at the top.

name: Tricep Pushdown
steps: Place the band just above eye level.
Take a few steps away until the band is taut.
Push your hips back slightly.
Extend and flex at the elbows.

name: Barbell Shrug
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with both hands in front of you, just past shoulder width.
Bend forward slightly at the hips, keeping your back straight.
Elevate your shoulders as high as possible towards your ears, contracting the trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction briefly at the top.
Lower your shoulders back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Dumbbell Shrug
steps: Stand upright with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended by your sides, palms facing your torso.
Keep your back straight and your head facing forward.
Elevate your shoulders as high as possible towards your ears, contracting the trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction briefly at the top.
Lower your shoulders back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

name: Cable Shrug
steps: Stand facing a cable machine with the pulley set to the lowest position, holding the bar attachment with both hands in front of you.
Keep your arms fully extended and your back straight.
Elevate your shoulders as high as possible towards your ears, contracting the trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction briefly at the top.
Lower your shoulders back to the starting position in a controlled manner.
